div.p:
Labour to get thoſe things which are the 
                     Direct. 3 very Life and Eſſence of a Chriſtian;


thoſe things which are conſtituent of, and difference a Chriſtian from all others. Some of theſe things have been hinted already, in ſhewing what a Formaliſt wants; I ſhall touch upon them here, and add more. In general, Content not your ſelves to act as Chriſtians, or in doing what a Chriſtian doth; 'tis one thing to be and do as a Chriſtian, and another to be a Chriſtian. There are eſpecially five things which conſtitute, and are, as it were, ingredient into the very Eſſence of a Chriſtian.
